    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2024-03-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-10-22T14:03:49Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;This joint resolution nullifies the final rule issued by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau titled &lt;em&gt;Credit Card Penalty Fees (Regulation Z)&lt;/em&gt; and published on March 15, 2024. The rule lowers the safe-harbor cap on certain credit card late fees. In particular, late fees allowed under safe-harbor provisions must be capped at $8 when charged by a large credit card issuer. This cap is not subject to annual adjustment to reflect inflation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
